Description:
You arrive at a small Sahti village. The villagers watch you with silent curiosity, but no one speaks until an elderly man steps forward and addresses you.

He asks if you are here on behalf of the company to claim their share. 

Before you can respond, he informs you that the tides have not been very generous this season, and all the fish they have caught is all they have for food.
